description:
Interested in publishing your music research, but don't know where to start? Or do you have some experience with scholarly publishing, but need some guidance about how to make your work open access? The Music Library is offering a new workshop, "Where should I publish my music research?" which will take place online next Monday, November 18, 12:30-1:25pm. For registration and details, click the link in bio 👆

At the end of this workshop, participants will be able to:
- articulate the differences and the pros/cons between open-access and non open-access publications;
- identify a list of academic journals in music;
- use relevant sources to see the impact of journals;
- make informed decisions on where to publish music research based on specific situations.

Whether you already have something ready to be published or simply want to know more about the publishing options and the process, join us for the workshop!
